reland) 2022" rel="cite" href="/id/nisr/2022/54">S.R. 2022/54</a>, <a class="LegCitation" href="/id/nisr/2022/54/article/2/1/a" title="Go to The Environment (2021 Act) (Commencement and Saving Provision) Order (Northern Ireland) 2022 art. 2(1)(a)" rel="cite">art. 2(1)(a)</a></span></p></div><p class="LegAnnotationsGroupHeading">Commencement Information</p><div class="LegCommentaryItem" id="commentary-key-d6905443f4dbeddb6097853518c6adfd"><p class="LegCommentaryPara"><span class="LegCommentaryType">I309</span><span class="LegCommentaryText">Sch. 1 para. 10 not in force at Royal Assent, see <a class="LegCitation" href="/id/ukpga/2021/30/section/147/3" title="Go to s. 147(3)" rel="cite"><strong>s. 147(3)</strong></a></span></p></div><div class="LegCommentaryItem" id="commentary-key-1df4b985b34c8a6cf65f8ba175e65517"><p class="LegCommentaryPara"><span class="LegCommentaryType">I310</span><span class="LegCommentaryText"><a class="LegCitation" href="/id/ukpga/2021/30/schedule/1/paragraph/10" title="Go to Sch. 1 para. 10" rel="cite">Sch. 1 para. 10</a> in force at 17.11.2021 by <a class="LegCitation" title="The Environment Act 2021 (Commencement No. 1) Regulations 2021" rel="cite" href="/id/uksi/2021/1274">S.I. 2021/1274</a>, <a class="LegCitation" href="/id/uksi/2021/1274/regulation/2/i" title="Go to The Environment Act 2021 (Commencement No. 1) Regulations 2021 reg. 2(i)" rel="cite"><strong>reg. 2(i)</strong></a></span></p></div></div><h3 class="LegClearFix LegSP1GroupTitle">Procedure<span class="LegExtentRestriction" title="Applies to "><span class="btr"></span>U.K.<span class="bbl"></span><span class="bbr"></span></span></h3><p class="LegClearFix LegSP2Container"><span class="LegDS LegSN1No" id="schedule-1-paragraph-11"><span class="LegP1No" id="schedule-1-paragraph-11">11</span></span><span class="LegDS LegSN2No" id="schedule-1-paragraph-11-1">(1)</span><span class="LegDS LegRHS LegP2Text">The OEP may determine its own procedure, subject to sub-paragraph (2), and the procedure of its committees.</span>&#xD;</p><p class="LegClearFix LegSP2Container"><span class="LegDS LegLHS LegP2No" id="schedule-1-paragraph-11-2">(2)</span><span class="LegDS LegRHS LegP2Text">A meeting of the OEP is not quorate unless—</span>&#xD;</p><p class="LegClearFix LegSP3Container"><span class="LegDS LegLHS LegP3No" id="schedule-1-paragraph-11-2-a">(a)</span><span class="LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text">there are at least three members present, and</span>&#xD;</p><p class="LegClearFix LegSP3Container"><span class="LegDS LegLHS LegP3No" id="schedule-1-paragraph-11-2-b">(b)</span><span class="LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text">a majority of the members present are non-executive members.</span>&#xD;</p><p class="LegClearFix LegSP2Container"><span class="LegDS LegLHS LegP2No" id="schedule-1-paragraph-11-3">(3)</span><span class="LegDS LegRHS LegP2Text">The validity of any proceedings of the OEP is not affected by any vacancy among its members or by any defect in the appointment of such a member.</span>&#xD;</p><div class="LegAnnotations"><p class="LegAnnotationsGroupHeading">Commencement Information</p><div class="LegCommentaryItem" id="commentary-key-8fdc01a6903dffddadb61d13c1ee428b"><p class="LegCommentaryPara"><span class="LegCommentaryType">I311</span><span class="LegCommentaryText">Sch. 1 para. 11 not in force at Royal Assent, see <a class="LegCitation" href="/id/ukpga/2021/30/section/147/3" title="Go to s. 147(3)" rel="cite"><strong>s. 147(3)</strong></a></span></p></div><div class="LegCommentaryItem" id="commentary-key-45b5bec1eb76744e25e9dad36a938f89"><p class="LegCommentaryPara"><span class="LegCommentaryType">I312</span><span class="LegCommentaryText"><a class="LegCitation" href="/id/ukpga/2021/30/schedule/1/paragraph/11" title="Go to Sch. 1 para. 11" rel="cite">Sch. 1 para. 11</a> in force at 17.11.2021 by <a class="LegCitation" title="The Environment Act 2021 (Commencement No. 1) Regulations 2021" rel="cite" href="/id/uksi/2021/1274">S.I. 2021/1274</a>, <a class="LegCitation" href="/id/uksi/2021/1274/regulation/2/i" title="Go to The Environment Act 2021 (Commencement No. 1) Regulations 2021 reg. 2(i)" rel="cite"><strong>reg. 2(i)</strong></a></span></p></div></div><h3 class="LegClearFix LegSP1GroupTitle">Funding<span class="LegExtentRestriction" title="Applies to "><span class="btr"></span>U.K.<span class="bbl"></span><span class="bbr"></span></span></h3><p class="LegClearFix LegSP2Container"><span class="LegDS LegSN1No" id="schedule-1-paragraph-12"><span class="LegP1No" id="schedule-1-paragraph-12">12</span></span><span class="LegDS LegSN2No" id="schedule-1-paragraph-12-1">(1)</span><span class="LegDS LegRHS LegP2Text">The Secretary of State <span class="LegChangeDelimiter">[</span><a class="LegCommentaryLink" href="#commentary-key-7c29c795e6eea5f3e6d2f087d92019c9" title="View the commentary text for this item" id="reference-key-7c29c795e6eea5f3e6d2f087d92019c9">F53</a><span class="LegAddition">and the Northern Ireland Department</span><span class="LegChangeDelimiter">]</span> must <span class="LegChangeDelimiter">[</span><a class="LegCommentaryLink" href="#commentary-key-90e690ad3bed802b6fda888d3eb18f4d" title="View the commentary text for this item" id="reference-key-90e690ad3bed802b6fda888d3eb18f4d">F54</a><span class="LegAddition">, between them,</span><span class="LegChangeDelimiter">]</span> pay to the OEP such sums as <span class="LegChangeDelimiter">[</span><a class="LegCommentaryLink" href="#commentary-key-694da9335e117bfdf7ab0ca7cecd01b3" title="View the commentary text for this item" id="reference-key-694da9335e117bfdf7ab0ca7cecd01b3">F55</a><span class="LegSubstitution">they consider</span><span class="LegChangeDelimiter">]</span> are reasonably sufficient to enable the OEP to carry out its functions.</span>&#xD;</p><p class="LegClearFix LegSP2Container"><span class="LegDS LegLHS LegP2No" id="schedule-1-paragraph-12-2">(2)</span><span class="LegDS LegRHS LegP2Text">The Secretary of State <span class="LegChangeDelimiter">[</span><a class="LegCommentaryLink" href="#commentary-key-d2aef6dfc728ef1bf0dd8b310ecdac65" title="View the commentary text for this item" id="reference-key-d2aef6dfc728ef1bf0dd8b310ecdac65">F56</a><span class="LegAddition">, or the Northern Ireland Department,</span><span class="LegChangeDelimiter">]</span> may provide further financial assistance to the OEP (including by way of grants, loans, guarantees or indemnities) subject to such conditions as the Secretary of State <span class="LegChangeDelimiter">[</span><a class="LegCommentaryLink" href="#commentary-key-f93e1dc4d05b1b2acb72cdc16769b748" title="View the commentary text for this item" id="reference-key-f93e1dc4d05b1b2acb72cdc16769b748">F57</a><span class="LegAddition">, or that department,</span><span class="LegChangeDelimiter">]</span> may determine.</span>&#xD;</p><div class="LegAnnotations"><p class="LegAnnotationsGroupHeading">Textual Amendments</p><div class="LegCommentaryItem" id="commentary-key-7c29c795e6eea5f3e6d2f087d92019c9"><p class="LegCommentaryPara"><span class="LegCommentaryType"><a href="#reference-key-7c29c795e6eea5f3e6d2f087d92019c9" title="Go back to reference for this commentary item">F53</a></span><span class="LegCommentaryText">Words in <a class="LegCitation" href="/id/ukpga/2021/30/schedule/1/paragraph/12/1" title="Go to Sch. 1 para. 12(1)" rel="cite">Sch. 1 para. 12(1)</a> inserted (28.2.2022) by <a class="LegCitation" title="Environment Act 2021" rel="cite" href="/id/ukpga/2021/30">Environment Act 2021 (c. 30)</a>, <a class="LegCitation" href="/id/ukpga/2021/30/section/147/6" title="Go to Environment Act 2021 s. 147(6)" rel="cite">s. 147(6)</a><a class="LegCitation" href="/id/ukpga/2021/30/section/147/7" title="Go to Environment Act 2021 (7)" rel="cite">(7)</a>, <a class="LegCitation" href="/id/ukpga/2021/30/schedule/3/paragraph/29/7/a/i" title="Go to Environment Act 2021 Sch. 3 para. 29(7)(a)(i)" rel="cite"><strong>Sch. 3 para. 29(7)(a)(i)</strong></a> (with <a class="LegCitat